Climate change is one of the most serious issues in 21st century. This Shiny App, using data from https://www.kaggle.com/berkeleyearth/climate-change-earth-surface-temperature-data, visualizes global temperature from 3 aspects.

  1. A line plot to show temperature change across years for selected country. User can choose layers to add on the line plot: add uncertainty and fit a smoother. User can also specify the smoother parameter on the slider.

  2. A scatter plot to show the relationship between temperatures of two selected contries. User can choose the fit linear regression option which fits a linear regression line on the scatter plot.

  3. A bar plot to show average temperature by country arranged in a descending order.
